@NODE main  "Complex number Class implementation for AmigaTalk© 1998:"

   The @{B}Complex@{UB} Class is an implementation of complex numbers for the
   @{B}AmigaTalk@{UB} system.  Its parent Class is @{B}Magnitude@{UB}.

   Methods available for the @{B}Complex@{UB} Class are:
   @{FG SHINE}
   new @{FG TEXT}
     
     Initialize a new instance of the Class @{B}Complex@{UB}. 
   @{FG SHINE}
   realpart @{FG TEXT}

     Return the real number portion of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   imagpart @{FG TEXT}

     Return the imaginary number portion of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   magpart @{FG TEXT}

     Return the magnitude of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
@{I}
     WARNING:  There is no cross-checking to see if the magnitude
               is correct, use @{B}computeMag@{UB} or @{B}computeMagPhase@{UB} first! @{UI}
   @{FG SHINE}
   phasepart @{FG TEXT}

     Return the phase of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
@{I}
     WARNING:  There is no cross-checking to see if the phase
               is correct, use @{B}computeMagPhase@{UB} first! @{UI}
   @{FG SHINE}
   computeMag @{FG TEXT}

    Determine the magnitude of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number from the
    real & imaginary portions.
   @{FG SHINE}
   computeMagPhase @{FG TEXT}

    Determine the magnitude & phase of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number from the
    real & imaginary portions.  If the imaginary part is zero, an error
    will be reported!
   @{FG SHINE}
   realpart: newReal @{FG TEXT}

     Change the real number portion of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   imagpart: newImag @{FG TEXT}

     Change the imaginary number portion of the @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   magpart: newMag @{FG TEXT}

     Change the magnitude (class instance variable) of the 
     @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   phasepart: newPhase @{FG TEXT}

     Change the phase (class instance variable) of the 
     @{B}Complex@{UB} number.
   @{FG SHINE}
   coerce: aNumber @{FG TEXT}

     Transform @{B}aNumber@{UB} to an instance of Class @{B}Complex@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   conjugate @{FG TEXT}
    
     Compute the complex conjugate of the Receiver.
   @{FG SHINE}
   ~ @{FG TEXT}

     Compute the complex conjugate of the Receiver.
   @{FG SHINE}
   + aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Add a number to the @{B}Complex@{UB} receiver.  The number will
    be transformed to a @{B}Complex@{UB} if it's not one already!
   @{FG SHINE}
   - aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Subtract a number from the @{B}Complex@{UB} receiver.  The number will
    be transformed to a @{B}Complex@{UB} if it's not one already!
   @{FG SHINE}
   * aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Multiply a number by the @{B}Complex@{UB} receiver.  The number will
    be transformed to a @{B}Complex@{UB} if it's not one already!
   @{FG SHINE}
   / aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Divide a number into the @{B}Complex@{UB} receiver.  The number will
    be transformed to a @{B}Complex@{UB} if it's not one already!
    An error message is returned if @{B}aNumber@{UB} is equal to zero.
   @{FG SHINE}
   printString @{FG TEXT}

    Print the @{B}Complex@{UB} number as a @{B}String@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   == aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the Receiver is equal to @{B}aNumber@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   < aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the magnitude of the receiver is less than @{B}aNumber@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   > aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the magnitude of the receiver is greater than @{B}aNumber@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   <= aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the magnitude of the receiver is less than or equal to
    @{B}aNumber@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   >= aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the magnitude of the receiver is greater than or equal
    to @{B}aNumber@{UB}.
   @{FG SHINE}
   ~= aNumber @{FG TEXT}

    Test whether the receiver is NOT equal to @{B}aNumber@{UB}.

@ENDNODE
